---
target: config
version: 1
validations:
  - name: config-package-exists
    type: file_check
    path: src/config/config.go
    contains:
      - "package config"

  - name: config-struct-defined
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "type Config struct" src/config/config.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: profiles-map-in-config
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "Profiles" src/config/config.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: default-config-function
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "func GetDefaultConfig" src/config/config.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: default-profile-function
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "func GetDefaultProfile" src/config/config.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: get-profile-function
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "func GetProfile" src/config/config.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: validate-config-function
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "func ValidateConfig" src/config/config.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: load-config-function
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "func LoadConfig" src/config/config.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: merge-config-function
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "func MergeConfig" src/config/config.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: config-tests-pass
    type: command_check
    command: go test ./src/config/...
    exit_code: 0

  - name: config-defaults-sensible
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify that GetDefaultConfig returns sensible defaults:
      1. Default profile has provider "claude"
      2. Default profile timeout is 5 minutes
      3. Default profile retries is 3
      4. Default profile includes default tools (bash, file_read, file_write)
      5. Default output directory is "build-default"
      6. Log level is "info"
      7. Profiles map contains a "default" entry
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/config/config.go"]

  - name: config-validation-checks
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify ValidateConfig performs proper schema validation:
      1. Checks version is present and supported
      2. Checks profiles map exists and has "default" key
      3. Checks each profile has a valid provider
      4. Checks CLI provider profiles have a command
      5. Returns []core.SchemaViolation (not error)
      6. LoadConfig calls ValidateConfig and returns errors on violation
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/config/config.go"]
---

# Config Validations

Validates the configuration system loads, saves, and merges correctly with sensible defaults. The config now uses agent profiles instead of flat agent config, and includes schema validation to catch invalid configuration early.
